  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Description\nWhile syncing during long periods of non-finalization, our the fork-choice chainhead can get stuck on a dead-end block making teku appear to have stalled.  We should add logs / metrics that make it easier to see what's happening in this case.  \n\nFor example:  the following chart displaying `beacon_head_slot` vs `beacon_slot` makes it appear that teku is stuck.  It may be helpful to add another metric that tracks the latest block synced: ![Screen Shot 2020-07-14 at 4.59.54 PM.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5b2bbbcb8f620008aaa30877/449bd117-c575-4f9e-a1f6-94f1ee2775a8)\n\nFor notes on reproducing, see description from #2157: https://github.com/PegaSysEng/teku/issues/2157#issuecomment-657725103",
